  "description": "Equipment To Test Air at Home!",
  "body_html": "<p><em>Disclaimer: this is not an endorsement of any product, just a record of my thinking. Also, none of this is medical advice. Also, be reasonable with what to expect from public spaces and your home behaviour. </em></p><p>I want to start doing more physical experiments. And instrumentation is a big part of that. So I bought a <a href=\"https://www.temtop.co.uk/products/m2000-2nd?variant=43848500216063&amp;country=GB&amp;currency=GBP&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gad_campaignid=19681366441&amp;gbraid=0AAAAAovfMCCiMFgncd8LUSf3ZSR8XEFoH&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjwlaTGBhANEiwAoRgXBaEvZHjJZeCdzhoUzJTwEo8HVKq86itPtFvMdweVOnikEucymnJRuhoCARYQAvD_BwE\">Temtop m2000 air quality monitor</a> that measures CO2 concentration, PM2.5 and PM10 particle concentration, temperature and humidity. I chose this one mainly because it also had data export and time recording. It was \u00a3120. </p><p>I\u2019m keen to start doing some home experiments with this. The first one I\u2019m planning to do is measuring the air changes per hour of my room with some dry ice as a tracer gas. I also want to do stuff with home made air purifiers, like Corsi-Rosenthal boxes and test if they work as good as people claim them to. I also want to figure out optimal fan placement. </p><p>I\u2019m not obsessive about measuring stuff in general, but it was pretty fun to see numbers go up and down on the monitor of this shiny new thang. </p><p>First, I checked to see if the CO2 level in my house makes sense. Most standards recommend &lt;= 1000pm in indoor spaces, so this is fine. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-1A4!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg\" width=\"3024\" height=\"2644\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a6d65237-7b7c-4ce7-be2f-a36203595eee_3024x2644.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:2644,&quot;width&quot;:3024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:1416627,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/i/173785222?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac0521bd-1e82-42ae-bc39-d4d3c9b37b33_3024x4032.jpeg&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;o